properties.areaDesc: Southern Inner Channels; Dixon Entrance to Cape Decision Coastal Area
properties.headline: High Wind Warning issued January 29 at 3:19PM AKST until January 30 at 9:00AM AKST by NWS Juneau AK
properties.description:
The National Weather Service in Juneau has issued a High Wind
Warning, which is in effect from 3 AM to 9 AM AKST Thursday. The
High Wind Watch is no longer in effect.

* WHAT...Southeast winds 35 to 45 mph with gusts up to 65 mph.


* WHERE...Portions of the southern Inner Channels and the
southeast Gulf Coast including Ketchikan, Craig, Hydaburg, and
Metlakatla.

* WHEN...From late tonight through Thursday morning.

* IMPACTS...Damaging winds could blow down trees and power lines.
Widespread power outages are possible. Improperly moored boats
and aircraft may break loose from their tie-downs.
properties.instruction:
Monitor the latest forecasts and warnings for updates on this
situation. Fasten loose objects or shelter objects in a safe
location prior to the onset of winds.

A high wind warning means a hazardous high wind event is expected
or occurring.

NWSheadline: HIGH WIND WARNING IN EFFECT FROM 3 AM TO 9 AM AKST THURSDAY
